## Key Concepts

- Impersonation Chain :
user->Security-sa->Workload->resource 

- TokenCreator Role: Required for generation access tokens on behalf of another SA

- IAM Conditions: Add contextual logic (time-based) to access conrtol 

- Condional vs unconditional Bindings: unconditiona overrides conditional 

- Times-based lockout: using request time to enforce access windows 

- 403 PermissionDenied confrims IAM is enforced correctly 

- Storage IAM Limitations: Bucket iAM does not support IP-based conditions

- Short-lived tokens: No key files required; safer and auditable 



